    - ADR-014 cites for tenant isolation (4 sites): all REMOVED or replaced with "no ADR; see FR-06 pending decision" pointer. ADR-014 is scoped to AI caching key conventions, not index-document tenancy.
    - CLAUDE.md (root): no ADR-014/ADR-004 cites found — no change needed.
    - Out-of-scope drift noted: `docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md:177,481` cite ADR-014 in non-caching contexts (SSE no-buffering, dual output paths). These are separate drift issues, NOT in FR-06 scope (which targets tenant-isolation + idempotent-reindexing pair).
    Owner action: confirm option (b) is acceptable, OR direct creation of new ADRs (option a) for tenant-isolation and idempotent-reindexing principles.
